I’ve been pretty nervous about finally saying this out loud, but here we are. After 5 years @buzzfeed, I’ve made the decision to move onto the next chapter of my life. A lot of thoughts, emotions, feelings, maybe some tears, because change is terrifying!!! But with discomfort comes growth, and maybe that’s a good thing. 

I’ll forever be grateful for what was maybe the most eventful five years of my life, for the brilliant people I got to work with, and for everyone who took a chance on me. More oversharing in this video that took a while to record because it felt so… raw. I’m anxious but also excited??? New year, new me 😤😤😤 I won’t let y’all down.

thank you again everyone for your kind words throughout the week 😭 And happy lunar new year 兔 you!! bit of a special one this year with mama lam here, pls scroll to feast on her made from scratch (!) works of art:

hi hong kong, i’m so happy to be back 🥹

a recap of some of my favorite meals in #hongkong so far:

- beef brisket and squid ball noodle @on_lee_noodle_shop & this incredible thick toast with ice cold butter - no, really!! it makes for the creamiest bite. also there’s nothing quite like Hong Kong milk tea 🥹

- curry fish balls and fish paste siu mai at 通達食店, omg the way I used to come here for a secret post school snack before heading home after classes 😭 it tastes exactly like I remembered and honestly, that alone makes it extra special to me 

- charcoal grilled bbq pork and roast pork from this one place in Prince Edward that imo, is some of the best I’ve ever had. I’m reheating the meats here because we bought… a lot 🌝

- this shrimp trio @sushiro.hk, my god, conveyor belt sushi has never been THIS good. this price, this quality!!!! I stan

- froyo from @yomamafroyohk 👀 this froyo was the fuel of my secondary school years. it’s the only place that does it as tart as I like it 😤

- a straight up feast at Oi Man Sang Dai Pai Dong that was out of this world, ty @lucas.sin for introducing me to this god tier food

- my mom’s hk-style borscht soup 🥹

- @tamjai_samgor 👑 broth like no other…

mama lam is BACK by popular demand, lol 😌✨a new video! and now we have milk bread for days, and i am so ok with it. 

speaking of exciting things though, pls keep swiping to hear more in this little excerpt I took out. I promise it’s worth it. it involves… a product of my own in development, and a balmuda toaster giveaway. actually wait, it’s two. two toasters 🌝 but really, I would love to hear from you all, so check out the questionnaire if you can! link in bio for ease of accesssss. 

questionnaire will be closing on 3/17 at 11:59PT, and remember to complete it in its entirety to be eligible!

introducing, some extra (eggstra??) custardy brioche french toast cubes, made with one of my favorite ingredients ever, eggs. #ad

truly so, very, excited to be working with @IncredibleEgg again, because i had such a great time making all the egg creations last year, and you know how much i love a creative medium - there’s honestly just so much you can do with even just one egg! also wanted to take this chance to say the biggest thank you (again) to everyone who voted for me last year – i can’t believe we won?!!! you all are the reason why i’m returning as host for the third annual #TheIncredibleEggCompetition this year, and i’m so looking forward to seeing the fantastic things our amazing lineup this year will bring. there are three rounds total, with a different theme each week. and this week, we’re starting it off with The Dozen Egg Brunch, because a carton of eggs can go a long way, even, into creating an entire brunch menu. here’s my take on it, channeling those cozy cafe aesthetics, with my french toast cubes, a tamagoyaki platter, fancy fruit tarts, and a yuzu kiwi mocktail, what do you think? 

remember to go check out the other creations this week by visiting http://bit.ly/425T7l5, and vote for your favorite this year! 

note: for food safety always ensure eggs are cooked to 160F! and for recipes calling for the use of uncooked egg whites, please remember to use pasteurized eggs.

a little photo dump and a hi from taipei 🌝

also, solo karaoke was a great success.
Part 1 of my little food coma-inducing street food tour at lin jiang #nightmarket 🥲 part 2 coming soon but I see y’all are loving the sausage garlic keychains

a recap of my favorite meals in #taipei rn, even though 10 slots is nowhere near enough: 

- hot pot @chanchihotpotlab where they let us take the leftover broth in a bag back home 🥹 get the mixed pot, get the shrimp paste, drink the broth - you will also want to take it home. 

- fresh mochi at ningxia night market, straight out of the pot and into a mountain of black sesame and peanut powder. my god. they also have a shaved ice version, i must go back 😤

- peking duck @silkshouse_taipei, the way we almost finished this entire duck even on full stomachs 🥲 so tender on the inside, so crispy on the outside, one of the best I’ve ever had and I say that as a Peking duck fanatic, 100% worth it winner material

- the freshest renbing @linlinangbing inside yongle market, where everyone has mad skills, from the core ingredients, to the assembly, to the speed at which they make the crepes, holy 🤯 i had this soaking up the sunshine, outside on a bench as a soft breeze passed through, it was magical af and it’s one of those bites i’ll forever come to associate taipei with.

- this bowl of Q at Jiufen Yuyuan at Linjing Night Market, with chonky sweet potato and taro balls, and brown sugar boba, over ice. all of my greatest weaknesses.

- i’m usually not a fan of pork liver but @shinyehtaiwan has completely changed my perspective. I didn’t even take a proper photo of it because I was so skeptical at first💀 but the texture was refreshingly… bouncy? and this sauce, oh my gosh, this sauce that clings onto the outside is otherworldly. i was this close to licking the plate clean istg. also pls try their almond tofu, it is also life-changing. 

- this strawberry apple cake from  @sunnyhills.taiwan, where they strongly encouraged I give this a try instead of going straight for the usual pineapple cake. It was indeed the right move, THANK YOU. 

- this fluffy kaya toast @longtail.taipei because ofc bread’s going to make it onto the list. Sorry for the terrible photo, it was an eat first, camera later moment 

- dumplings at 錢櫃 ktv/karaoke. Iykyk 🫡

the second part of my street food adventures at the linjiang #nightmarket in #taipei 🌝 personally though, I do like my stinky tofu extra stinky

edit: no the fried chicken is not edible 🪦

and so my taipei solo adventure comes to an end, for now. but i’ll be back, very very soon, to this happy place of mine. no more pandemics pls 🥲 @regenttaipei, my forever favorite, thank you for a wonderful time, and for letting me take self-care to a whole new level 🥹

hello to these creamy deviled eggs, but make it ~cute~ 🌝 #ad best thing about these baby chicks is that i actually repurposed decorated easter eggs to make them 🤫 getting two uses out of these eggs means double the fun, you know, there's really no substitution for the amount of joy they bring me heh. and this flavor!!! a little bit of miso and some kewpie also made these 😩👌 eggstra creamy. 

also featuring turmeric pickled egg flower baskets that have a much more herbaceous take, feat. basil, parsley and avocado, just in time for spring hey hey. 

give these cuties a try this season and remember to vote for your favorite @incredibleegg creation at https://bit.ly/3LqdXW! #TheIncredibleEggCompetition

and a quick tip - remember to use hard-boiled eggs within one week of cooking, and any recipe utilizing hard-boiled eggs should be refrigerated and consumed within 2-3 days! 🥚
here to share my new favorite song, top tier grammy-winning lyrics 😌

i take my role as an eggbassador very seriously 😤 but it’s time for me to pass on the baton and crown our new egg champion of the year 🍳 #ad genuinely in awe of all the creations this year, and the sheer variety!!! this versatility is legit why eggs are one of my favorite ingredients to have fun with, though right now, i’m working on mastering the kichi kichi omurice 🤫 pls send tips

can you tell how many egg recipes had a cameo in the vid btw 🌝 bonus points if you can list them all out below. #TheIncredibleEggCompetition

i’ve been feeling a little melancholy lately. or maybe it’s nostalgia? i’m not sure what it is. 

maybe it’s because of my recent travels. of finally returning to places i’ve called home after many years, only to realize the meaning of home has shifted, and there’s a strangeness that comes with what was once familiar. there are things i miss that i’ll never be able to find again, and this urge to fill that emptiness, but maybe that, is what evokes this feeling of… saudade.

…anyways, I guess the first pic is also proof that bread has always been there for me.
happy monday, here’s my real what I did over the weekend #vlog 🙃

ok can i just say, that the food scene in orlando is actually… incredible??! #ad i feel like i never got to experience the city beyond its iconic theme parks, but my most recent food-centric trip has seriously, shown me a whole new world. 

here’s what i ate in 24 hours:

- started the day with desserts @sampaguitaicecream, including but not limited to an ube-cream covered ube brownie, a gorgeous halo halo that was larger than the size of my face, and... basically a sampling of every ice cream flavor they had, because everything looked so perfect?? the soy sauce butterscotch and keso guava cheesecake were 🤌🤌 they even had a pineapple cake flavor!

- this gigantic grilled squid @zasianvietnamesekitchen served with a homemade jalapeño green sauce by chef huong, who seriously puts so much heart and thought into her restaurant. fr, this sauce was so good (the ideal tangy sweet), i actually ended up bringing some home. it's sitting in my fridge right now, but not for long 🌝

- yakitori, craft cocktails and more light bites at what is now maybe my favorite restaurant in orlando - @toritoripub. i only had two days in the city but i still went here twice 🙃 the chicken oysters and the karaage are insane. also, that crunch on the karaage 😩👌

- omakase!! in orlando!!! kind of love the on-the-go standing sushi concept @edoboysushi, and that we got to pick which ones we wanted specifically.  also, the energy in here was fantastic 🔥 

there's so much more beyond what you see here too - like how i became obsessed with the coffee and croffles @haancoffeeroasters etc... truly, thank you @visitorlando and everyone i got to meet at these locations for introducing me to the many sides of orlando we’ve never known before. the entire experience was seriously, Unbelievably Real 😌 next time you’re in the city, now you know!!!

when @tictacusa asked if i could make a baked good inspired by their new strawberry & cream flavor, i knew immediately i had to make these pocket-sized strawberry cream cakes. kind of like the mini lunchbox cakes i made a while ago, only it’s even more compact, and perfect for personal consumption on the go. just like tic tac mints heh 🌝

i really wanted to capture that feeling of going on a multi-layered flavor adventure, so here we have it! with fresh strawberries + airy chiffon cake + fluffy whipped cream + its extra creamy cousin mr. mousseline cream 😌 what do we think?? #TicTacUSA 🍰 #ad

never getting over these iconic poses, zoolander would be so proud. happy #mothersday to my og pose #queen ✨

hi from the Boston airport!! i’m early for my flight and totally ok with it because there’s a new lounge by @chasesapphire Reserve in town and my god is it next level - no, but it’s actually one of the best i’ve ever been to. #ChaseSapphirePartner if you see me irl, i will also be gushing about this, because this place really feels every bit like an oasis in the chaos of travel - pls scroll to the last pic for me in prime relaxation.

the sheer elegance of this place and the thoughtfulness that went into every part 🤌 hello to this gorgeous, gorgeous bar with specialty cocktails, to select menu items carefully designed by the great @douglasswilliams (both ready to eat and made to order!!), local brews served in a signature taproom + coffee from @atomiccoffeeroasters— they even have all you can eat biscotti!! 😳 there’s also a whole area dedicated to wellness too, where you can cozy up in a rest pod, or, spend your waiting time in an anti-gravity massage chair... complete with an LED face mask - it’s wild, and i’m obsessed.

the lounge is officially open today (!!) and will be available to Chase Sapphire Reserve cardmembers with a Priority Pass membership, along with up to two guests. so next time you’re in Boston... 👀

it’s only 6am and i’m already losing my mind 🙃 #art

i get asked a lot about what i do when i’m not making content, and honestly? most of the time, i’m just trying to make sure my soul is happy. 

it’s a hard balance, trying to keep a level state of mind in this game that rewards numbers over caliber. but that, is the reality of this world. and as important as it is to keep moving with the wave, it’s my safe harbors and anchors that help me keep going, when i’m ready to. 

so thank you, to everyone who’s been part of this journey so far. your presence means a lot 🙇🏻‍♀️

thank you @tatlerhongkong for this feature 🙇🏻‍♀️ there’s always so much i want to say about what goes on behind the scenes, but i never know where or how to start. so it really means a lot to me, to be able to share these thoughts about mental health, this era of hustle culture and… this never ending work cycle, on a platform like this, especially in the 852.

sharing some of my favorite bits, but go give the full article a read! maybe some of it will resonate with you…
japan!! you’re stunning and i’m so happy to be here 🥹

being able to have tsukemen at 8am is already the dream, but to find out that the #ramen shop is THE @rokurinsha_official??! truly unreal. this broth is ✨phenomenal✨. v grateful for jet lag, and for the decision to stay at a hotel right next to #tokyo station, because idk how else i would’ve made it out this early - it really is the key to avoiding those long wait times 🫠

i missed you Osaka!!! 🐙

i remember staying at the namba oriental hotel just 2 minutes away from this takoyaki stall over a decade ago. every night, my brother and i would order a dozen of these, and devour them as fast as we could. one, because they’re that good yes, but also mostly so we could claim more balls as our own, even if it meant burning our mouths half the time. siblings, you know 🙄

now i get them all to myself. can’t break the habit of eating them fast, and oof it burns, but they taste just as good as i remember them to be 🌝
7-eleven in #japan hits different every time 🤌🤌🤌also, im sorry— fresh fruit smoothies?? at #7eleven???? next level.
hello #korea 🥵 you make my mouth burn, but my stomach very happy. maybe a little too happy.

i like to think that the stars magically aligned for me to be able to be in #korea the day this #croissant heaven had its grand opening ✨ getting there 30min and standing in the heat before it opened was WORTH IT 🥲 I’ve heard much about @nu_dake and was a little wary tbh, but this new location that just opened yesterday is 🤌🤌 

croissant #pizza? croissant onigiri? croissant crocs? they have it all. you can’t escape the buttery 🥐 i’ve never been surrounded by this much ~cwoissant~

#ad quick break from travel content to say hello to one of my favorite drinks of the summer - @dunkin Cold Brew concentrate + tonic water + orange juice 🤌  i know you’re thinking... what?? oj??? but really, i swear by it. it’s the perfect icy fizzy zesty, still pleasantly bold, but so very refreshing. especially in! this!! heat!!
i want so badly for this 24-hour #ramen convenience store to be everywhere 🥲 no matter what time of day, ramen is here 4 u

currently in a food coma but hi from my favorite #taipei!! 🥹 here to share some of my top food highlights so far:

1 & 2: the iconic taiwan railway bento, the taste of nostalgia, and a pork chop so big my chopsticks were really struggling 

3. the braised pork rice, pork knuckle and cuttlefish rice noodles at huang ji braised pork 🤌 no need to go to jin feng for a meal that’s equally as satisfying

4. literally went to the night market just to get this bowl of boba and taro/sweet potato balls over ice at 九份芋圓 

5 & 6. ultimate breakfast at fu hang soy milk, and the joy it brings, even with the 45min wait 🫠 the fantuan was also fire

7. my first bite in #taiwan, steaming hot black pepper bun at raohe night market that I ripped into so fast, my tongue died- sorry for the terrible photo
 
8. don’t sleep on @bafangtw!!!!! this was only $5 i—

9 & 10. these pineapple buns baked fresh at raohe night market, served with a slice cold butter, hk-style. literally found it by following the smell of… freshly baked bread. the crust is crispier, the bun is fluffier/lighter - makes for a phenomenal bite 😩

did we know that @haagendazs_us has yogurt?!!? #ad i didn’t until i saw these at @walmart a few weeks ago, right before this travel whirlwind, and as a huge haagen dazs fan, i can tell you, it’s... exactly what i wanted it to be. creamy, luscious, with speckles of vanilla bean, just like their ice cream 🥹 perfect timing too because i’ve been wanting to try making the viral yogurt-covered fruit bites, and 😮‍💨 this touch of peanut butter really made them the ideal sweet and savory 👌

social_posts.post_text: it’s crazy hot over here in tainan but this second visit to the city really has been wonderfully restful. ty for the warm welcome @silksplacetainan 🥹 pls swipe to the end for my current status after drinking half of 36 alcoholic tea shots at the bar 🙃

i’m sorry it took so late to come back, #tainan 😭 but to the place so often overlooked by many, myself included, you’re amazing - there truly are, so so many highlights. also seriously feels like almost every other place had a line outside, the food journey never stopped 🫠 here are a few favorites but there’s so much more to try:

1 & 2. the legendary win chang beef soup, where every beef dish was fresh af, and almost everything was to a perfection I didn’t think was possible 

3. this boba milk tea shaved ice, need i say more. but as I’ve heard the locals say, go to 冰鄉!

4. this guava coffee @barista_ray that I got two days in a row because it was truly that good - nothing like I’ve ever had before, with a perfectly balanced real fruity sweetness 🥹

5. this beautiful scallion pancake at dadong night market that dadong’ed my heart. the expertise that went into creating these thin layers, that amounted to the crispiest, flakiest scallion pancake I’ve ever had 🤌🤌🤌

6. truly the best deal for a protein-packed donburi, and y’all— unlimited winter melon lemon tea

7. a mascarpone cheese soft serve with raspberry sauce @ninaogroup that we waited 30 min for - worth it

8. pork lard rice - a must try everywhere, but especially at ding fu fa 

9. I could dedicate an entire post to just the cafes alone in tainan. the aesthetics, the quality 😩 sicily style coffees are also now my official favorite, and this is the place that started it all

10. If you find fresh egg rolls being made anywhere in #taiwan, don’t think twice, just get it.

time always flies by so fast in #taiwan 🥲 the bliss a giant bowl of spicy beef noodle soup brings, with a glass of fancy boba tea no less. thank you @regenttaipei for always being the best home away from home 🥹 and for packing the cutest to-go breakfast for my 5am airport ride, pineapple cakes included and all 🙇🏻‍♀️ 

until next time, 886!

as promised, here are those 36 shots of tea #cocktails i was telling you about in #tainan. never had this much tea… and alcohol in one night 🫠 highly recommend going with a group of friends, don’t be like me 🫢

if I’m being honest, i saw red bean mochi pie and immediately ran to the closest mcd in #japan 🏃🏻‍♀️💨 why do the international #mcdonalds always hit so hard!!! also, happy mid autumn festival! eat mooncakes, or… shrimp nuggets.
i gave in and tried the ai yearbook thing, and now im determined to make one of these my halloween costumes 🙃 but which one of the 6??

can confirm i was 99% boba after this multi-course #boba meal 🧋 but i still want more boba, do I have a problem??

will be back next time to get the boba marshmallow pizza too 🥸 #taiwan

went on a bread hunt in tokyo, and this one’s to all the breads and pastries i’ve loved before in #japan 🍞 the absolutely bookmark worthy bakeries, imo:

1-3. the cream of the crop. stunning croissants and the closest level i’ve ever gotten to a god tier baguette. also love that they had two versions, soft or hard - opted for the softer which has a slightly chewier texture, and a crust that won’t destroy the roof of your mouth (not that I mind either ways). go in the morning, get them fresh 🤌 @pain_des_philosophes 

4-6. this is what people dream of when we see the word shokupan.  the definition of what we mean by “pillowy-soft” - my biggest regret is not being able to gently toast this in my balmuda toaster, but can you imagine @centre_the_bakery 

7. it might be a chain, but beard papa truly never disappoints. the airiness of the cream puff + velvety smooth custard combo hits so hard everytime. also this ratio, hello??

8. ngl, this place was all over my fyp and i was very skeptical. but I take it all back. i’m sorry I doubted you, @i.m.donut , you are indeed, donut like i’ve never known before. they’ve somehow perfected a dough that is not too dense, nor cakey. kind of a perfect blend of a mochi donut x yeast donut? also, the lemon one is out of this world, I’m serious. no custard filling or anything but the zesty flavors come through beautifully. 

9. honestly just really loved the shape of this croissant, which maximizes the ease of dunkage into a warm cup of latte. delightful. @bricolage_bread_and_company 

10. don’t ask, just go to @donki_jp

hi! this is a nerdy appreciation post for @fishkillfarms in upstate new york, where i was just at this weekend, with my haul of 54 apples (10 different varieties!!) and an even deeper love for the apple world after 2 fantastic hours of apple hunting 🥹

i love, love, love apple picking, but half the time, i feel like I don’t know what I’m picking exactly?? but they’ve clearly spent a lot of time mapping out the farm for visitors - what’s ripe, what’s not ready, where what is. also I’m a sucker for illustrated maps. but my favorite thing was the little descriptors they put for each apple variety, a bit of fun history, and more importantly: what they’re best used for, for maximum enjoyment 🤌 

also devoured two fresh apple cider donuts while brainstorming what to do with these apples - any suggestions? ✍️ and yes, will absolutely make some tarte aux pommes with this super tart caville blanc d’hiver 🍏

it’s my favorite time of year 🥹 #ad the season of golden colors, oversized sweaters, and pumpkin spice. which!! contrary to popular belief, has no pumpkin, but all the nostalgic notes of cinnamon, ginger, cloves and nutmeg 🤌

maybe that’s why drinking #pumpkin spice lattes, like this one made with @dunkin pumpkin spice K-Cup® pods, always makes me feel like i’m wrapping myself in a fuzzy blanket... brb, going to play some laufey to max out cozy vibes 😮‍💨
the level of bento boxes in #japan is truly unmatched 🤌 the choices, the packaging, the quality - i swear i was only going to get one, i don’t know how i ended up with 4 🙃
a little asia travel dump feat. many of the people (and doggos) who made it so great 🥹

before i moved to nyc, i was actually in la for three months. i’d moved to the city of dreams with no job, no friends, no concrete plan - nothing but a suitcase full of dreams. the days were split between serving at a hot pot restaurant, and driving 3 hours to and from the OC to work as an unpaid intern. the nights were spent relentlessly editing and re-editing job applications, 99% of which i never heard back from. in retrospect, i’m grateful for the things i learnt then. but in the moment, it was maybe one of the lowest points in my life. i was terribly homesick, lonely, but too ashamed to admit to my family that i felt like a failure.

food from the san gabriel valley was what brought me a lot of comfort during this time. the fantuan from huge tree pastry, the chicken rice at savoy kitchen, the shaved ice at sinbala… but this place especially: dai ho restaurant - this is the chicken soup that nourished my soul. to this day, the first sip of their beef noodle soup is the closest i’ve ever gotten to an anton ego ratatouille moment. 

today marks the first time i’m back at dai ho after six long years (they were closed the last four times I tried to come 🥲) and it’s just as I remember it to be, if not even better. thank you for being here throughout all this time 🥹
a full stomach gives me so much serotonin 😤 can you see why taiwan night markets are one of my happiest places

back in japan for a hot second and this weather 🤌 these colors 🤌🤌 fall is a 1000/10 here. 

also, happy thanksgiving! here’s your annual reminder to wear sweatpants all day today. i had sushi instead of turkey and it was great.
i just wanted to keep this moment in time with me forever - truly living out my studio ghibli dreams right now 😮‍💨
my personal color analysis report says i’m a winter bright, but fall will always be my favorite 😌

#ad taking a small break from Japan content to say that, i got to try some cambodian food for the first time on my philly food adventure recently, with friends and @zellepay 🌝 and— truly, one of the best feasts I’ve ever had!! from coconut fish curry (amok), to pumpkin soup, to bitter flower salad - I think bitter flower is my new favorite ingredient? I’m not used to bitter as a flavor component in dishes, but it’s oddly refreshing, and goes so well with the sweet, tangy and spicy 🤌

also got to meet the incredibly talented family behind sophie’s kitchen - from the front of house to master of the kitchen, they do it all. they’re truly wonderful, do stop by when you’re in town!!
can i just say i had a jolly good time in LA 🍔🍔
the man, the myth, the legend, @kichikichi_omurice !!!! 🥹🥹🥹🥹 and the best #omurice I’ve ever had. i don’t know if i can ever recreate this but i’ll try my darnedest just to have a taste again.
life off the internet lately 🥹
hello and happy holidays from the lam fam! we finally got a proper christmas tree this year… also learnt that my brother makes v good blistered shishito peppers, im so proud 😤

what a year 2023’s been… there’s been a lot of refiguring things out, a little bit of blundering and making the occasional mistake 🥲 but there’s also been lots of learning and some truly great adventures. i’ve been going at my own pace, slowly rediscovering moments of inspiration, and I like to think that we did ok?? 

still, 2024 will be even better, even if i feel like a bag of nerves rn. here we go 😮‍💨 happy new year!
